// LayersPanel
// Left-side panel showing the scene tree for the design editor.
// Lists all nodes top-to-bottom (reversed child order so top layer appears
// first). Supports click to select (with Shift for multi-select), expand/
// collapse for group nodes, and visibility toggle per node.

layers is re-derived from SceneGraph.walk() on every sceneVersion change.

FUNCTION LayersPanel() -> JSX                                          EXPORT
  Reads sceneVersion and selected IDs from designEditorStore.
  Computes layers via SceneGraph walk (reverses child order for top-first display).
  Renders a tree list; groups are expandable via toggleExpand.

---

FUNCTION toggleExpand(nodeId) -> void
  Adds nodeId to expanded Set if not present; removes it if present.

---

FUNCTION handleClick(nodeId, shiftKey) -> void
  Calls store.select([nodeId], shiftKey) for additive selection support.

---

FUNCTION toggleVisibility(nodeId, currentVisible) -> void
  Calls updateNodeWithUndo({visible: !currentVisible}) for the given node.
